+otherTeamPlaybooksHeader('Artifact Collectors')
.sheet-ArtifactCollectors.sheet-OPB
	input.sheet-triggerbox.sheet-ExpToggle(type='checkbox', name='attr_Toggle-Team-Moves-Unused', value='1', checked='')
	+move("ArtifactCollectors-Move","<b>Check the Manifest:</b> You have a list of known artifacts, and the stories and rumours associated with them. When you <i>look up a mystical effect</i>, ask “What can do this?” and roll +Sharp. On a 10+, you know exactly which artifact you’re looking for. On a 7–9, you narrow it down to three likely candidates. On a miss, this is something new—you have no idea what to prepare for.",true)
	+move("ArtifactCollectors-Move","<b>I Smell Fudge:</b> There’s an extensive list of sensory experiences tied to different sorts of powers. When a team member <b>reads a bad situation</b>, the Keeper will tell them if a phenomenon is at work here, before they spend any hold.",true)
	+move("ArtifactCollectors-Move","<b>Where in the World?:</b> When a team member <i>deliberately leaves clues or rumours to lead someone to a particular place</i>, roll +Cool. On a 10+, your targets appear when and where you planned. On a 7–9, they’re suspicious and come prepared. On a miss, you tipped your hand. They might set a surprise for you.",true)
	+move("ArtifactCollectors-Move","<b>Quicktime:</b> When team members successfully <b>help out</b> or <b>protect someone</b> facing booby traps or phenomena-related hazards, they turn the trap in their favour. Choose one: deal the hazard’s harm to something, or change the environment in a way that helps the hunters.",true)
	+move("ArtifactCollectors-Move","<b>You’re Not Worthy:</b> When a team member <i>calls out a selfish or oblivious owner of an artifact</i>, the team takes +1 ongoing to foil their plans.",true)
	+move("ArtifactCollectors-Move","<b>Something Different:</b> Take a move from another team playbook.",true)
	+move("ArtifactCollectors-Move","<b>Change Team Style:</b> Pick a new team style. You now use that one instead of the one you first chose.",true)